         <abstract>
            <p>A short Gǝʿǝz theological treatise which is
              a translation from Arabic. In the early Church this kind
              of text was recited for the baptized faithful after the catechumens had been dismissed.
               Whilst <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName>, as the central celebrated ﬁgure,
               was described and praised without his name being mentioned directly,
               the initiated in the mysteries of the Christian faith knew who was intended.</p>
               
               <p>Not to be confused with the text also known as <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2444Temher">Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt</ref>.
               For the texts in the version than cannot be immediately identified, see
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6688TeachingMysteries"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT6688TeachingMysteries</span></ref>.</p>
         </abstract>
